<plot>Presented in black and white, the look of "Of Note" represents the colourless world of Johnson (Adam Barrett). He is a young man, stuck in a lifeless, soul crushing job. His drab existence is turned upside down by a seemingly innocuous event. Someone has left a pink stick-it note on one of his files, reading; 'If you could choose something different, would you?' This sets the wheels in motion for Johnson, who must figure out who sent the note and what it all means, all the while trying to avoid the wrath of The Boss (Henry Woolf).</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?407534</url></doc>
